<br>
I have read all the post about what kind of raiding and looting rules we should use and i see that there is a certain disagreement among us. I have therefor decided that I will post the rules we will us from now on. I will have the privilege of changing these rules in the future if needed. If changes are done in the future i will post them under this subject in this forum.<br>
I also have the privilege to remove RP from any persons that have not behaved in a good way during a raid.<br>
<br>
Introduction<br>
<br>
First of all as i see it we will have two kind of raids:<br>
a) Unofficial raids<br>
b) Official raids<br>
<br>
First we need to distinct between these to forms.- Therefor the rules that makes a raid official are:<br>
<br>
1. It MUST be announced at least 4 days in advance on this forum<br>
2. At least one officer must attend during the whole raid (this is to make sure that the raid points are given out correctly and that all betting with points will be done in the right way).<br>
<br>
All raids that does not live up to both of these criterias will be accounted for as unofficial raids and will therefor not give any raidpoints.<br>
<br>
Rules of Unofficial raids:<br>
<br>
1. Unofficial raids will have no special rules regarding looting. The rules for these raids will just be whatever the persons within the raid have decided on. <br>
<br>
2. Complains about looting from unofficial raids must first be taken to any of the officers and if not decided by them taken to me for my decision. <br>
<br>
3. There is no need for an officer to be present at unofficial raids. <br>
<br>
4. There is no need to announce it in advance.<br>
<br>
<br>
Official raids<br>
<br>
Except for the rules that must be followed to make a raid account as a official raid these rules also apply:<br>
<br>
1. Raidpoints<br>
<br>
1.1 All people that participate in a official raid will receive one (1) raidpoint (RP) per hour rounded up.<br>
<br>
1.2 The reward for showing up at epic fights or single Boss encounters will be 2 RP<br>
<br>
1.3 Arriving late or leaving early on a raid will half the raid points you earn. (With late i mean arriving after the scheduled time at the scheduled meeting place for the raid and with leaving early i mean that you leave before the raid is finished). This is to encourage folks to come in time because there is nothing more frustrating than doing a raid and having all arrive 30 mins to late.<br>
<br>
1.4 In addition to the above there might be special occasions where you are able to obtain RP i e a tournament.<br>
<br>
1.5 RPs must be allocated to the MAIN char ONLY. What I mean is Regardless of what alt is raiding, you have one total account with ALL your RPs earned on ALL raids your alts took part in. ANY of your alts can bid on any item (NBG again though, mustn't forget) using ALL your total RPs. --- For foreigners again: Any Ron can bid using Ron's total RPs pool.<br>
(This is a good point by Firm and makes it easier to organize the RP because of fewer &quot;accounts &quot; with RP)<br>
<br>
2. Looting and spending RP<br>
<br>
2.1 All loot (including money) that is not NO DROP MUST be looted by either the Raid leader or someone that is appointed to looting by him. This person is referred on to as main looter or ML. The ML must be either the RL or an officer.<br>
<br>
2.2 All money earned and all items of less value (that will not be betted RP on) will be given to the guild bank.<br>
<br>
2.3 All NO DROP items that drop and and all other good items will be betted on by using RP (The NO DROP will be betted on during the raid and the other items after the raid).<br>
<br>
2.4 The betting will be a &quot;closed betting&quot;. That means that all persons that can wear the specific item (including the persons alts) are free to bet on it by sending a tell to the ML and saying how many RP they bet. There can only be one round of bettings per person on each item. It is then the MLs responsibility to announce who has the highest bet and what that bet was. <br>
<br>
2.5 In the case of 2 bids the same or more, they will tell each person their number ie 1 and 2, then use a /ran 1 2<br>
command and whoevers number is shown they spend their points and get the loot. (Thanx Hairy for this good point should have missed it if you did not post it).<br>
<br>
2.6 Complains on the betting will be brought up with the ML first, then with the officer on the raid and if not agreed upon with me.<br>
<br>
2.7 The raid leader will have the privilege of reserving one item (the item needs to be posted in the forum in advance and they need to inform the raid about the item they reserved at the start of the raid) that they can wear for themselves but they will then recieve no RP for the raid. If they choose not to reserve any items or the reserved item does not drop they will instead be given double the RP for the raid. (This is to encourage folks to make more raids and wanting to be raidleaders themselves).<br>
<br>
2.8 The RP spent after or during a raid MUST have been earned before the raid. You are not allowed to bet RP that you have earned during the raid or will earn during the raid.<br>
<br>
2.9 If a class specific item drops that only one person in the raid can wear or only one person wants to bet on they will receive it without the loss of RP<br>
<br>
3. The responsibility of the Raid leader<br>
<br>
3.1 The raid leader (RL) is responsible for allocating RP and also noticing spent RP after the raid and informing the raid points manager (RPM) witch is Silvar. There will hopefully be a post on the board with the updated RP all the time.<br>
<br>
3.2 The RL is responsible for overseeing that all members of the raid is taken care of (retrieving corpses and so on)<br>
<br>
3.3 The RL is responsible of taking care of the looting or appointing a person that is responsible for that.<br>
<br>
3.4 Any complains about the way the RL managed the raid will be taken first with the RL and then with any officer and finaly with me.<br>
<br>
<br>
4. The responsibility of the ML<br>
<br>
4.1 The ML is responsible of doing all looting (except No DROP items ) during the raid.<br>
<br>
4.2 The ML is responsible for giving all the money and not good items (that will not be betted on) to the guildbank.<br>
<br>
4.3 The ML is responsible for administrating the bettings on items and for telling the winner and how many RP he/she betted.<br>
<br>
<br>
5. The responsibility of the raid members<br>
<br>
5.1 The raid members MUST follow the instructions of the RL<br>
<br>
5.2 The raid members are free to quite the raid before its finished but all RP earned in the raid will then be halved.<br>
<br>
<br>
Well thats about it I think. I have probably forgot a whole bunch of stuff but i will modify and make corrections later.<br>
