<br>
I am sad to hear that Firm/Trooper disagrees so much with theese rules so that he´d like to quite the guild. My intention with theese rules are certainly not to make anyone leave the guild. I however certainly will not hold any hard feelings against anyone that disagrees with the rules or have comments about them.<br>
<br>
I have tried hard to take all the different comments on the forum into account. But my rules are not and where never intended to be a mix of all oppinions. I have instead listened to the different approaches and made rules out from what I think would benefit raiding and the guild.<br>
<br>
But i would like you all to just stop for a second and look back on this fact. Why are we all playing EQ? Why do we want raids? How many raids have we had so far?<br>
<br>
I realy think we all play EQ because its fun. The raiding should also be fun and be special events that can give us all a better sense of teamwork and maybee an oportunity to get some new gear for are chars.<br>
We have not in the past done many raids. We have been a small guild and we have had problems even finding groups of guildies at times. But a new era is comming! We have grown in levels and numbers! We now have the possibility to do raids at least at medium levels. This is fun! This should give us a even better EQ experience! But before we start raiding we have had a long discussion about who should be able to bet on what loot with how many points and soo on. I think we should have rules but lets never forget that wer have not tried them out yet. There might be comments on the rules ive posted and there might be disagreements but lets try to raid first and then do corrections. The reason i posted rules was to bring and end to the discussion and to enable us to do the fun and important stuff witch is raiding!<br>
If anyone feels that they can not accept theese rules I am sad but i cant force folks to stay in guild. But I say concentrate on raiding and have fun not on arguing about the rules because we can change them if it is obvious that they are wrong and we have had NO raids yet to see how they work.<br>
<br>
Let me give u a short not about why i think we need rules:<br>
<br>
<br>
1. Someone needs to be in charge of deciding the rules<br>
<br>
As you have seen in the forum as soon as more than one person is in charge of the final decision there will be different approaches to how to do certain things. To minimize the frustration of that i have taken my responsability as the guild leader to do the final rules.<br>
<br>
<br>
2. Rules will minimize conflict between memebers. <br>
<br>
As you have seen in the forum there has been a discussion on what rules for looting and RP there should be. There has mainly been two different approaches on how things should be done. I have read all the posts before posting my rules and i have spent literaly hours twisting and adjusting the different oppinions so get theese rules that ive posted. I am aware that they are nowhere near perfect and that we might need to adjust them after a while. My clear thought is thought that we should make adjustements AFTER we have made a few raids so that we first will have time to see how things work out. (I have also stated this in the beginning of the rules that there might be modifications in the future).<br>
<br>
<br>
As i have said i have read all the posts and i think there has mainly been two big issues that have been discussed. <br>
<br>
* Hidden or open auctions<br>
* Loot/RP for the raid leader<br>
<br>
There has also been some discussions about how many RP should be givven and so on.<br>
<br>
<br>
Hidden vs open auctioning<br>
<br>
I am and have always been a true fan of transparency! However i think that once we all grow and are able to raid more and more difficult places we will encounter more NO DROP loot. The problem with NO DROP loot is that it needs to be actioner right away. Because of that i think a hidden system makes auctioning faster, safer and in some ways more fair (i e the person that makes the last bet knows how much all has betted in an open auction). I am aware with the problem that accusations of cheeting might come up more in a hidden system thats why the ML should always tell the raid who won and how many RP that person spent on the item. In that way all can feel relatively safe that the person that won used more RP than you did in your bet. I cincerely think this is the best system on the paper but as i said before lets raid a bit and if im proven wrong ill have NP with changing it.<br>
<br>
<br>
Loot and RP for the Raid Leader<br>
<br>
I think we all agree we want more raids! To encourage peeps to raid more there should be a bonus as a Raid Leader.<br>
As i see it i would like to give the raidleader something extra for the work he/she has done to research for the raid and the responsabilitys of i e collecting the corpses for the dead raid members.<br>
This would encourage folks to raid more and be RL themselves.<br>
There could be two ways of doing this. Either the RL gets more RP or he gets some other priveliege (like a free loot).<br>
If you consider epic fights with drops i think it is quite clear that if i e Firm started and managed a raid to get a cleric epic drop and Leebe tagged along and had more RP than Firm it would not feel fair that she would be able to get the epic drop over Firm (at least that is what i think). So how would you then manage rules so it does not turn out that way? Well my rules does the following. Firm (the RL) has the advantage of choosing one item for himself (off course he needs to be able to use it, NBG). If Firm (RL) chooses that hed like the epic drop he will automaticly loose all the RP he earned during the raid. This system is good for making folks wanna try epic fights to get drops but it in my opinion does not give the RL to many advantages because they recieve zero RP idf they choose one item.<br>
If the RL does not choose one item (the epic did not drop) they should still be given something extra i think for all the work they did to manage the raid. So in that case they get doubble RP.<br>
<br>
All in all this is a kind of combo between the two different approaches that have been on the forum where one wanted more RP for the RL and the other a free loot.<br>
<br>
All in all i realy have tried to make rules that do 3 things:<br>
<br>
* First and most important that stops the discussion and makes us focus on raiding and have fun!<br>
<br>
* That will make it rewarding to be RL so that many folks will want to start raids (I think raids are fun so i want many raids)<br>
<br>
* Makes all practical stuff on raiding easier  <br>
a) 1 hour= 1 RP, <br>
<br>
b) Punishing peeps who comes to late = raids start at time<br>
<br>
c) Closed auctions = faster auctions, <br>
<br>
d) Telling who won and spent RP = more transparency and you can compare the winning bet with your bet, <br>
<br>
e) RL gets the oportunity to reserve one item = more epic raids<br>
<br>
d) RL gets the oportunity to get 2 times the RP = more raids because more peeps wanna be RL<br>
<br>
etc. <br>
<br>
Anyway. This IS the rules we will start off with just to make sure we start raiding. If they need to be modified or you have comments on them plz tell me about it in the future and ill discuss that with you all.But lets not forget that the important stuff is to start raiding.<br>
Good hunt!<br>
<br>
